Package com.forgerock.opendj.util

Classes providing utility functionality.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Predicate<M,P>
    Predicates transform input values of type M to a boolean output value and are typically used for performing filtering.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ASCIICharProp
    A ASCIICharProp provides fast access to ASCII character properties.
    Collections2
    Additional Collection based utility methods.
    FipsStaticUtils  
    Iterables
    Utility methods for manipulating Iterables.
    Iterators
    Utility methods for manipulating Iterators.
    ManifestUtil
    Utility methods reading information from opendj-core's manifest.
    PackedLong
    Provides static methods to manipulate compact long representation.
    ReferenceCountedObject<T>
    An object which is lazily created when first referenced, and destroyed when the last reference is released.
    SizeLimitInputStream
    An implementation of input stream that enforces an read size limit.
    SmallSet<E>
    A small set of values.
    StaticUtils
    Common utility methods.
    StringPrepProfile
    This class defines the "stringprep" profile as defined in RFC 4518.
    SubstringReader
    A sub-string reader.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    OperatingSystem
    This class defines an enumeration that may be used to identify the operating system on which the JVM is running.
